{"body": ["<tr><th>Project/Area Number</th><td>11559004</td></tr>", "<tr>\n     <th>Research Category</th>\n     <td>\n      \n    <p> \n        \n        \n      <a href=\"/search/?qc=Grant-in-Aid%20for%20Scientific%20Research%20%28B%29\" class=\"link-page underline\">Grant-in-Aid for Scientific Research (B)</a>\n    \n    </p>\n     </td></tr>", "<tr><th>Allocation Type</th><td>Single-year Grants</td></tr>", "<tr><th>Section</th><td>\u5c55\u958b\u7814\u7a76</td></tr>", "<tr><th>Research Field</th>\n      <td>\n      \n      <a href=\"/search/?qd=%E5%BA%83%E9%A0%98%E5%9F%9F\" class=\"link-page underline\">\u5e83\u9818\u57df</a>\n      \n        </td></tr>", "<tr><th>Research Institution</th><td><a href=\"/search/?qe=The%20University%20of%20Tokyo\" class=\"link-page underline\">THE UNIVERSITY OF TOKYO</a></td></tr>", "<tr><th><h3><strong>Principal Investigator</strong></h3></th>\n          <td>\n          <h4><span><a href=\"/search/?qm=40011738\">TAGAI Touhei</a></span>\u00a0\u00a0THE UNIVERSITY MUSEUM, THE UNIVERSITY OF TOKYO, PROFESSOR,\u00a0\u7dcf\u5408\u7814\u7a76\u535a\u7269\u9928,\u00a0\u6559\u6388\u00a0(40011738)</h4>\n          </td></tr>", "<tr><th><strong>Co-Investigator(Kenky\u016b-buntansha)</strong></th>\n          <td>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=70256197\">NISHIAKI Yoshihiro</a>\u00a0\u00a0THE UNIVERSITY MUSEUM, THE UNIVERSITY OF TOKYO, ASSOC. PROFESSOR,\u00a0\u7dcf\u5408\u7814\u7a76\u535a\u7269\u9928,\u00a0\u52a9\u6559\u6388\u00a0(70256197)\n          <br>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=20172679\">NISHINO Yoshiaki</a>\u00a0\u00a0THE UNIVERSITY MUSEUM, THE UNIVERSITY OF TOKYO, PROFESSOR,\u00a0\u7dcf\u5408\u7814\u7a76\u535a\u7269\u9928,\u00a0\u6559\u6388\u00a0(20172679)\n          <br>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=20004450\">OHBA Hideaki</a>\u00a0\u00a0THE UNIVERSITY MUSEUM, THE UNIVERSITY OF TOKYO, PROFESSOR,\u00a0\u7dcf\u5408\u7814\u7a76\u535a\u7269\u9928,\u00a0\u6559\u6388\u00a0(20004450)\n          <br>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=00124595\">TAKATSUKI Seiki</a>\u00a0\u00a0THE UNIVERSITY MUSEUM, THE UNIVERSITY OF TOKYO, ASSOC. PROFESSOR,\u00a0\u7dcf\u5408\u7814\u7a76\u535a\u7269\u9928,\u00a0\u52a9\u6559\u6388\u00a0(00124595)\n          <br>\n          <a href=\"/search/?qm=50206596\">SUWA Gen</a>\u00a0\u00a0THE UNIVERSITY MUSEUM, THE UNIVERSITY OF TOKYO, ASSOC. PROFESSOR,\u00a0\u7dcf\u5408\u7814\u7a76\u535a\u7269\u9928,\u00a0\u52a9\u6559\u6388\u00a0(50206596)\n          </td></tr>", "<tr>\n     <th>Project Period (FY)</th>\n     <td>\n      <span class=\"fiscal_year\">1999\u00a0\u2013\u00a02001</span>\n     </td>\n    </tr>", "<tr>\n     <th>Project Status</th>\n     <td>\n      <span class=\"pstatus\">Completed(Fiscal Year 2001)</span>\n     </td>\n    </tr>", "<tr><th>Budget Amount\u00a0<a class=\"award_amount_help\" href=\"https://support.nii.ac.jp/kaken/project_details\" onclick=\"return winOpen(this.href);\">*help</a></th>\n    <td>\n     <h5>\u00a513,900,000 (Direct Cost : \u00a513,900,000)</h5>\n     \n     Fiscal Year 2001 : \u00a54,300,000 (Direct Cost : \u00a54,300,000)<br>\n     \n     Fiscal Year 2000 : \u00a54,800,000 (Direct Cost : \u00a54,800,000)<br>\n     \n     Fiscal Year 1999 : \u00a54,800,000 (Direct Cost : \u00a54,800,000)\n     \n    </td></tr>", "<tr><th>Keywords</th><td>DATABASE / COMMON FORMAT / MUSEUM / NEXT GENERATION / INTERPRETER / DEGITALIUZED IMAGE / HTML / \u5b66\u8853\u6a19\u672c / \u5171\u7528\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30de\u30c3\u30c8 / \u5171\u901a\u8a00\u8a9e</td></tr>", "<tr>\n      <th>Research Abstract</th>\n      <td>\n        <p>The informations on the database formats were collected in the many research fields and the possibility to introduce common format to the different research fields were discussed. The University Museum, the University of Tokyo and The University Museum, Kyoto university are constructing the database with a thought of the common format. The concepts and constructions of those two database systems are precisely investigated and the format for the database of the next generation is discussed.<br>The introduction of a common format to all the research fields is concluded to be ineffective because of great variety on the research fields.<br>The purpose of the introduction of a common format is only to attain a useful and convenient database for every research field. In order to accomplish this purpose, the possibility of a virtual common format was suggested. Every research field constructs its own database with own format. The central server system interprets the format to the common one. Then All the researcher outside of the system can access to the database without considering the hidden true format.<br>In the database system of the next generation should have those interpretation system.\n        \n        </p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>"]}
